  "instructions": [
    "Add chestnuts, onion, and garlic to pressure cooker.",
    "Add thyme, rosemary, broth, salt, and pepper to the pressure cooker.",
    "Close the pressure cooker and cook for 10 minutes at 120F.",
    "Preheat the comal to 375F.",
    "Once the pressure has released, carefully remove the chestnuts from the pressure cooker and peel them.",
    "Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add white rice to the saucepan and cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Add the milk, cream, and cooked chestnuts to the saucepan.",
    "Stir well and cook until the mixture starts to thicken.",
    "Transfer the pilaf to a serving dish and serve hot.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
